    "BANKERS SECRET PROFITS BARRED BY COURT RULING Alleged Usages and Customs of Wall Street No Defense Justice Gavegan Decides i NEW YORK October 27 Alleged j usages and customs of Wall street do not legally constitute as such a de fense against an action according to a decision handed down In the supreme court yesterday by Justice Gavegan The enurt also held that a hanker acting in a judiciary capacity must be able to show that he has made no se cret profits through the use of securi ties left in his care The decision was made In the suit of James Q Patterson president of the New England iranite Works against Raymond Pynchon Co bankers and brokers Patterson sued to obtain an account ng from the brokers and to restrain them from selling 1743 shares of stock which had been left in their care as security for an active account The shares he asserted had a peculiar val ue aside from their ostensible market value He charged that the brokers had used his collateral securities in making loans with banks pledging them for amounts greater than those due from him and making secret profits by obtaining certain rates of"
